parts.text: Based on my search, Python's sorted() function uses Timsort algorithm, which has O(n log n) time complexity in average and worst cases.

citedSources.title: Python sorted() - Built-in Functions
citedSources.snippet: The sorted() function returns a new sorted list from the items in iterable.

citedSources.title: Timsort - Wikipedia
citedSources.snippet: Timsort is a hybrid stable sorting algorithm with worst-case time complexity of O(n log n).

citedSources.title: What is the time complexity of Python's sorted()?
citedSources.snippet: Python's sorted() uses Timsort which has O(n log n) complexity.
